views.text: Neuroanatomy Netter Flash Cards - Part1 - AnkiWeb

For all medical students (as I am)(neurology rotations), residents, neurologists, and neurosurgeons who want and need to remember neuroanatomy very well and accurately, after purchasing Neuroanatomy (Netter Neuro Flash Cards) , It is better to remind one thing instead of ten inseparable things in each flash card or you want to repeat with your portable electronic device, especially on your lovely Anki app.

So I tried to make half of these flashcards completely to make this Anki deck.

I will do my best to finish the second part and share it with you as soon as possible. If you find this deck useful, please share it with anyone you know who might find it useful.
And finally, don't forget comment here, and as much as you can, please help me solve my problem (
)(or for more support contact me: ankifortoddler@gmail.com ) because after that I can turn all other resources(even those you suggested) into anki decks and share them with you for free, here.
Schematic of the Autonomic Nervous System
Inferior horn of left lateral ventricle in temporal lobe
After the file is downloaded, double-click on it to open it in the desktop program.
At this time, it is not possible to add shared decks directly to your AnkiWeb account - they need to be added from the desktop then synchronized to AnkiWeb.
Love it, hoping for a part 2!
The best neurology deck I have found so far. Thank you!

This is an amazing deck. Quality images, you can tell what structure the line is pointing to, super easy to blast through and not have to stop and make edits. I wish I had started studying neuroanatomy on this deck instead of scraping together a bunch of different sources. Is there a part 2?
